parameters.text:
=Score this candidate against this specific job.

CANDIDATE:
- Skills: {{ $json.candidate_profile.key_skills }}
- Experience level: {{ $json.candidate_profile.experience_level }}
- Projects: {{ $json.candidate_profile.notable_projects }}
- Certifications: {{ $json.candidate_profile.certifications }}

JOB:
- Title: {{ $json.title }}
- Company: {{ $json.company_name }}
- Location: {{ $json.location }}
- Description: {{ $json.description }}

Return ONLY:
{
  "match_score": 0,
  "matched_skills": [],
  "missing_skills": [],
  "recommendation": "apply",
  "reason": "",
  "seniority_mismatch": false
}

Scoring method:
1. List the CORE required skills from the job description (ignore nice-to-have requirements like "X years experience", university status, or soft skills)
2. matched_skills = core requirements the candidate has evidence for
3. missing_skills = core requirements the candidate lacks
4. match_score = (matched / total core) × 100, adjusted:
   - +10 if candidate has a relevant project or certification
   - -15 ONLY if the job explicitly requires senior/managerial level (5+ years)
5. recommendation = "apply" if match_score >= 35, else "skip"
6. For fresh-graduate candidates: entry-level, junior, internship, and associate roles should almost always be "apply" if 2+ core skills match
7. reason: 1-2 kalimat Bahasa Indonesia, sebutkan skill yang match dan yang kurang

